Hanco’s is truly stellar and I’m so glad they survived they’ve stayed in business. The sandwiches are awesome, the staff gets specifications right and they got the pho to me with the broth still warm.
My go-to place for beef pho, bubble tea, and bahn mi. The interiors could be better but good enough. Popular after-school destination.

Sandwiches are really great! Have been going since they had that little tiny place on Bergen Street. Just wish the ladies working more friendly. It was almost as if they were upset that I was their spending my money with them.
Love this spot. Prices went up.
I love the grilled pork banh mi here but I've had almost everything on the menu and its all great!

Quick, delicious and relatively inexpensive.

I’ve been visiting Hanco’s for years and it’s always a fresh & flavorfully consistent experience - even through this pandemic. My favorite: vermicelli salad with vegetarian pork.  Support this small business at this location or on Montague.

I tried the summer roll and the grilled chicken banh mi.  The summer roll tasted very earthy. It’s difficult to describe, almost like unwashed lettuce. Also, in my personal opinion, small amount of shrimp in there.  Grilled chicken banh mi was average.  Good for a try!
I miss Hanco’s. I’ve been in Atlanta for 4 years now and there is no Hanco’s. I need a banh mi and almond bubble tea right now!
Ordered takeout of classic sandwich, a salad, and some rolls and it was great! I would add pork to everything :) so worth it

Ordered online and was given an estimate of 35 minutes. Almost one hour later and nothing. I called the location to see what was happening and the woman on the line was completely unapologetic. She curtly said the delivery guy was outside and it should be another 15 minutes then nothing. This doesn’t come as a surprise since the staff at Hancos are almost always sour.

Great sandwich a couple of years ago but the quality went way down since new management or owner took over  I got food poisoning from a chicken banh mi... awful coordinated attack from both directions

banh mi that bangs 🔥

No frills Vietnamese fix.

I love their Bubble tea and Vermicelli Salad. You can tell them how sweet you want the tea. If you don't have sweet tooth the no sweet version is what you should order Their Rice Vermicelli Salad has a very well balance of sour and sweet. It is very refreshing and light.

Summary: convenient local chain with ban mi, phô, and other Vietnamese dishes. Quick service, clean, reasonable prices. The phô we had was warm (not hot) and was average in taste - but a good value for the price point.
The banh mi is on point and the soups always good. The place is frequently busy, but the wait never seems too long and the smells from the open kitchen get you in the mood while you're waiting.

Hands-down favorite place for pho in the area - love coming here especially on a cold day. Banh mis and bubble tea are also very, very good. It can get quite busy during lunch (haven’t really been here for dinner so can’t speak to that) but there’s usually enough space to sit.
Get the shredded chicken sandwich. Yum!

Grilled Chicken Banh Mi was delicious. No frills kind of joint.
Service is good, can be busy at around 2:40, because that's when the kids from ps261 get dissmised.

Great Ban mi sandwiches! I had Tofu ban mi and it was awesome!

The place is really nice with just a super chill atmosphere. Both our meals were thoroughly enjoyed for the most part. The Vietnamese coffee has quite an intense taste; it tasted better to me after it had been diluted. Definitely recommend this place altogether.
Pho is quick and delicious. My go to
Green salad with grilled pork is delicious 😌
Quick and easy ordering. Food was great, although the tables were a bit dirty. Definitely need to try the bubble tea next time.

Honestly the best Vietnamese food I’ve ever had. The pho and banh mi aren’t nearly as good anywhere else. The bubble tea is also fantastic and there are dozens of options. Whenever I order delivery it arrives incredibly quickly. On top of all of this, Hanco’s has some of the best vegetarian fake meat options by far. I would recommend this restaurant for anything from a quick bite to a sit down meal.
Food is good BUT... if you’re black you will get looked at and they will see if your money is real lol like come on Hanco
I totally enjoyed the food and the atmosphere at this restaurant. I definitely recommend.
Best Pho in this Area!
Best ban mi sandwiches ever never had a bad experience

I’ve tried this place a couple times each time seamed to be worst than the next. 1 time-good broth boring but still better then most pho in Manhattan and close to my work 2 time- hair I pho 3rd- banh mi sandwich, the traditional pork. It had a lot of good vegetables but the meat had to much of an seasoned porky taste that is unappetizing. 4th- I realized what I should have realized all a long. The broth is way to boring and the portions are way to small for $10 pho, they don’t give you much noodles or broth they also don’t have tripe. What they make coast no more then $3 In Materials. They are jacking up the price because it is a hipster neighborhood, hipster don’t really care about food nor do they no good Vietnamese food. It is sad when people realize how to take advantage of people and then choose to do so. Greed is a very powerful thing. I will not be going back to hanco’s

delicious tofu sandwich. if u have any dietary restrictions, make sure to ask bc ingredients are not listed (my own mistake that i didnt check the coffee has milk in it, or the sandwich mayo). nice seating area; clean bathroom.
One of my local go-to's when I want clean fresh healthy tasty food.
Some of the best bahn mi I have ever had. Definitely get a side order of spring rolls as well.

Very solid Vietnamese food here with that hipster vibe. The food is very good but I wouldn't call it great. If I crave a decent Pho or Bahn Mi sandwich I'd come here but if I want something top notch I'd hop on the train into Chinatown. The pricing is expensive but I do take into account the area it's in. It does get crowded here at night for the dinner rush so sometimes even ordering takeout can be a bit of a wait.
This is my favorite Vietnamese spot in the neighborhood!
Good pho for a reasonable price. Bubble tea too, though definitely get full sugar as they use much less than other places to begin with.
The banh mi is very good. Vermicelli is decent. Boba is not that good, needs more sugar.

The food is delicious! I have only had the Vietnamese Sandwich with Vegetarian Chicken. Looking forward to trying the Phớ.

Eat healthy, eat at Hanco's. Small space but that shredded chicken sandwich calls my name. Great sandwich. May make your place smell like hell but the taste is heavenly. A large drink in this place is a small, every where else. Grab a fresh lemonade with that shredded chicken sandwich and you are done for the day. Thank you Hanco!

Not 5 stars because nothing is perfect lol. Had my first Bahn Mi there and now I crave it on a weekly basis. SO GOOD. My partner and I usually get one of those, but the phos are good too and he really loves the shrimp spring rolls as well.
The Pho and vermicelli were both good. The pork is good, chicken was a fail.
Good Vietnamese food, although a bit pricey for what it is. The boba drinks are also not bad. Better than gong Cha and Kung Fu tea in my opinion.

This is a neighbourhood gem that I frequent or order from regularly. Their beef pho is delicious and fresh and comforting. Additionally, I can never resist an extra order of fresh summer rolls. The banh mi are also very good and when I occasionally order them, the meat seems hot off the grill, and the vegetables fresh.

We always ordered 2 Beef Pho noodles basically. At the first time, there were lots of beef meats and tendons (especially tendons were 4-5 pieces for 1) so we ordered 2nd time, too. However, there were no tendons for 1 person’s. Nothing of tendons really!!! Also, 2 of 2 noodles had only 2 pieces tenders. We thought they just made a mistake so we ordered 2 beef noodles this 3rd time with 1 EXTRA mains(beef and tendons) but there were ONLY 1 piece of tendon and few more of just beef meats for both. How it can be same that ‘regular’ and ‘extra’ had same only 1 piece of tendon??? We paid more mains for extra!!! How can they explain it? This is not the accident, right?? They just welcome to 1st time.
This Vietnamese restaurant has never let me down, I highly recommend their Sandwiches, Pho, and Bubble Tea!

Everything are above average, service is nice and fast, also have a website that you can order online. As a fast food stop, their pho may not be complete(no tendon, meatball or strip) but are decent. Bubble tea are pretty good. I love their vermicelli, it’s delicious and easy to take out.
I ate a grilled chicken sandwich and have had stomach pains all day.
Great service, food, and bubble tea. Not a lot of seating, so order out if you have to. Their other location has two floors though.
Great food for the price 👍

Had a classic Banh Mi and a Vietnamese iced coffee. Both were really good! This is a nice little spot with some good food. I would recommend it if you're in the area. Go with the Banh Mi really worth it! Price isn't too bad as well.
Our go-to for bahn mi and pho.

My go to Vietnamese spot in Brooklyn Simple, no frills - what’s good? Pho (they have beef, pork, chicken & vegetarian pork and vegetarian chicken) & Vietnamese sandwich - my fav is the classic Vietnamese sandwich ($7.25) & the beef pho ($9.50) 🍲 Green tea bubble tea iced (small $3.75, med $4.25) is great or their Vietnamese coffee (love the condensed milk in it) with bubbles

I didnt finish my soup and you can ask them for to-go container. Will go back tomorrow.

I ordered grilled chicken banh mi (ordered it spicy) and summer rolls, with a green tea lemonade.  The banh mi was better or as good as any I've had. They added jalapeño slices to make it spicy but still needed sriracha. The size was wholesome.  This was the first time I had summer rolls so I can't compare, but they were good, minty and light. The peanut dipping sauce was necessary if you want strong flavor.  The green tea lemonade was really good, had some kind of basil or mint taste in it.  Overall I'll come here again.

This is a great vietnamese spot. Delicious food, cute and clean restaurant, and pleasant service. I would highly recommend the grilled pork sandwich. It is amazing, and a go to lunch or dinner option. The pork is delicious, the carrots, cucumbers, and radishes (which I normally do not like) are surprisingly tasty, and add a nice crunch, and the cilantro adds a cool, and refreshing bite. Another one of my favorites is the grilled pork noodle soup. I've heard the bubble tea is also great, though I haven't tried it myself. I hope you enjoy the outstanding restaurant.

This restaurant is a marvel of efficiency and wonderful to watch. The servers, kitchen staff and delivery people are all buzzing in harmony. Within minutes of ordering, my pork buncha appeared fresh from the kitchen. I live a 15 min walk away and hope they continue to prosper  and one day open a new branch in park slope! There's Chipotle level potential here if they keep up their excellence.

Hanco's, back at it again!  This is the location closest to my apartment, so I come here the most often.  It's the same good menu as the other two, I usually get a veggie pork banh mi with an iced Vietnamese coffee and doing so keeps me very happy.  This location is right next to the Bergen FG stop, so if you're coming from north east Brooklyn or the LES it's probably the best Hanco's for you.  This location is also around the corner from the tiny store front that Hanco's started in,  which I miss because it was cluttered and romantic but at least the new places and the renovations symbolize the good success they've had. One of the only bahnmi places I could find near Brooklyn Heights, I had to try this place. I had the regular bahnmi sandwich with the taro milk boboa tea. Nothing to complain about the food. I've had better at Chelsea market, but this is a nice place to stop by and enjoy lunch

Awesome sandwiches

Hanco's has relocated to 134 Smith Street and this is a review for that location since I couldn't find it's new profile. I ordered a beef pho to go and the portions were a bit imbalanced. There was hardly any pho but I have to give them props that there was a good amount of beef slices in there. I like how they put red onions in the mix which is a first that I have seen at a pho place. It adds a nice zing to the dish and the broth was decent. I prefer Nicky's Vietnamese at nearby Atlantic Ave for their broth but Hanco's version did taste lighter and healthier. I love pho and thought it was decent. Just wish it didn't cost almost $10 for it.

My favorite restaurant, I know the number by heart! The spicy tofu sandwich is AMAZING! It can get crowded, but the service is fast and it's a comfortable atmosphere to sit and eat in. I would HIGHLY recommend it!
Cool, original place

Sometimes you want to go, where everybody knows your order.  I've somehow never tired of their terrific tofu sandwich, and I probably eat it once a week.  It gets a little bit crowded at times, but it's perfectly pleasant and the food is delicious.
Once we got here with my friend after we came back from hockey game  - were hanging around Brkln))) We had really tasty sandwiches. Nice place.
Enjoy the summer rolls, a Tofu Sandwich and refreshing Lichee Bubble Tea. Limited seating, so get it to go.
Solid option. Later hours on Sunday now (plus!). Shreaded chicken banh mih is tasty. And they take you seriously when you say spicy! Extensive bubble tea options too. Speedy delivery.

salad is fresh and delicious (get it with grilled chicken), the banh mi are tasty (I like Classic or Shredded Chicken, extra spicy). I'm not into bubble tea, personally, but I like the Vietnamese coffee. Delivery can be slow sometimes but the delivery guys are super nice.

At least that I know of.  I'd say asking for it to be spicy got me about one touch spicier than I'd prefer, but sometimes I'm in the mood for that amount too.  The bread is nice, well toasted, and the ratio of fillings to bread is very nice.
